item.description:
 Revert Git Commits Let&rsquo;s keep this first simple by focusing on a simple, yet helpful, git change. Sometimes mistakes are made and commits need to be reverted. There are two options depending on whether the commit has been pushed or not.
Commit not pushed git reset HEAD~1
Commit pushed  git reset --hard &lt;desired_commit&gt; (eg. 57f05fgds) git reset --soft HEAD@{1} git commit -m &quot;Revert to 57f05fgds&quot;
